Re: -ndehanaiga
by furrykef » Tue 09.06.2011 8:59 pm The simplest explanation is:お前の気持ちも分からんではないが = "It's not that I don't understand you, but..."I'm thinking the ん here must be doubling both as the negation for 分かる and for the so-called "explanatory の". In other words, the の is getting contracted to ん, but you can't have んん, so the single ん suffices for both.
